cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.PL. 

The paper deals with software maintenance and information retrieval techniques to identify suitable search terms for software change tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also extensively uses information retrieval techniques such as TextRank and POSRank, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques to analyze the task description, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with natural language texts, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves identifying locations in the source code, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
